        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(memory-core): Memory Privacy Audit + Encrypted Backup",
        "body": "## Summary\nBuild the first contribution as **privacy visibility plus encrypted backup**, not live encrypted memory. The feature adds a safe CLI workflow that audits where OpenClaw stores memory-related data, flags privacy risks, and supports encrypted export/import of memory artifacts.\n\n### Key Changes\n- Add CLI commands:\n  - `openclaw memory privacy audit`\n  - `openclaw memory export --encrypted --out <file>.age`\n  - `openclaw memory import --encrypted --in <file>.age --target <dir>`\n- Audit reports:\n  - memory workspace path\n  - `MEMORY.md`, `memory/*.md`, `DREAMS.md`, `memory/.dreams/`, and dreaming reports\n  - SQLite/vector index path and size\n  - embedding provider classification: local, remote, none, or unknown\n  - Active Memory transcript persistence state\n  - plaintext memory surfaces and backup risks\n- Encrypted backup:\n  - export creates a tar archive of selected memory artifacts, then encrypts it\n  - output uses the `.age` format via the TypeScript `age-encryption` package\n  - import decrypts into an explicit target directory\n  - import refuses to overwrite existing files by default\n  - no live memory files are changed during export\n\n### Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Adds memory privacy visibility plus encrypted backup/restore at rest. This proof covers `openclaw memory privacy audit`, non-empty `openclaw memory export --encrypted`, and `openclaw memory import --encrypted` after merging current `main` and resolving conflicts in commit `944bb2e052`.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Isolated local temp lab only: `<redacted-local-proof-root>`, with `OPENCLAW_HOME` pointed at `<redacted-local-proof-root>/home`. The normal production OpenClaw home was not used. The temp proof directory was removed immediately after the run.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n```console\n$ export OPENCLAW_HOME=<redacted-local-proof-root>/home\n$ export OPENCLAW_MEMORY_BACKUP_PASSPHRASE='non-secret-proof-passphrase'\n$ node openclaw.mjs memory privacy audit\n$ node openclaw.mjs memory export --encrypted --out <redacted-local-proof-root>/memory-backup.age\n$ node openclaw.mjs memory import --encrypted --in <redacted-local-proof-root>/memory-backup.age --target <redacted-local-proof-root>/restore\n$ shasum -a 256 \\\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md <redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/MEMORY.md \\\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/DREAMS.md <redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/DREAMS.md \\\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-05-29.md <redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/memory/2026-05-29.md\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the isolated lab run:\n```console\ncommit=944bb2e052\nPROOF_ROOT=<redacted-local-proof-root>\nOPENCLAW_HOME=<redacted-local-proof-root>/home\n--- audit ---\nMemory Privacy (main)\nWorkspace: $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace\nEmbeddings: openai (remote)\nSession transcripts: not found (0 files)\nArtifacts:\n  memory-file · present · 1 files · 13 B\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n  memory-directory · present · 1 files · 19 B\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory\n  dreaming-artifact · present · 1 files · 12 B\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/DREAMS.md\n  dreaming-artifact · missing\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.dreams\n  index · present · 1 files · 8.0 KiB\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/memory/main.sqlite\n  sessions · missing\n    $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\nFindings:\n  warning remote-embedding-provider Memory embeddings use remote provider \"openai\"; memory text may leave this machine during indexing/search.\n  warning plaintext-memory-artifacts Memory, dreaming, or session artifacts are stored as readable local files.\n  warning memory-index-present A memory index exists on disk and may reveal keywords or semantic metadata.\n  action encrypted-backup-available Use `openclaw memory export --encrypted` to create an encrypted backup before moving or archiving memory.\n\n--- export ---\nEncrypted memory backup written: <redacted-local-proof-root>/memory-backup.age (3 files)\n--- import ---\nEncrypted memory backup restored: <redacted-local-proof-root>/restore (3 files)\n--- restored sha256 ---\n7478557d49e64bc7bab77fbf78eda7a6ca5e0c1d73999ae887cf860efd9efb67  $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n7478557d49e64bc7bab77fbf78eda7a6ca5e0c1d73999ae887cf860efd9efb67  <redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/MEMORY.md\n7ed6c1b91736edbabe911206e16b0a4a1346f1b839af80dbaa982f17f3b58664  $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/DREAMS.md\n7ed6c1b91736edbabe911206e16b0a4a1346f1b839af80dbaa982f17f3b58664  <redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/DREAMS.md\n8f1fdb6b274414d6c214466cc418d68072ecc3eea9be8d5605c4af327fb60638  $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-05-29.md\n8f1fdb6b274414d6c214466cc418d68072ecc3eea9be8d5605c4af327fb60638  <redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/memory/2026-05-29.md\n--- restored files ---\n<redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/DREAMS.md\n<redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/MEMORY.md\n<redacted-local-proof-root>/restore/memory/2026-05-29.md\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The audit detected the non-empty lab memory artifacts and warned about plaintext memory/index surfaces and the configured remote embedding provider. The encrypted export wrote a `.age` backup containing 3 files. The encrypted import restored 3 files, and SHA256 hashes matched between source and restored `MEMORY.md`, `DREAMS.md`, and `memory/2026-05-29.md`. The isolated proof directory was cleaned up after the run.\n\n**What was not tested:** Live encrypted memory is intentionally out of scope for this phase. I did not test the production OpenClaw home; all proof used the isolated temp lab above.\n---\n\nCommunication contact: kothapallianandsagar@gmail.com\n\n",
